        "text": "I think the term microservices is overused but one advantage of separating out different parts of the system to individual components unlike flumine’s monolithic architecture is that restarting specific components to pick up new config can be a lot less painful than restarting the entire system \n\nI have considered config file watching in the past; you could alternatively implement an API that lets you modify your internal state (as well as read it - facilitates monitoring and other GUI applications)",
        "team": "T4G9NBD2M",
        "user_team": "T4G9NBD2M",
